The paper deals with the recognition and drawing of a specific type of intersection graph, namely Stick graphs. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses algorithms for testing the existence of Stick representations, which falls under data structures (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper presents results about graphs that are not Stick representable, which falls under graph theory (cs.GR).
